Hi! I need help! I can't figure out why I cant get a second column in my blog body for a rich text module. Here is my body code, where did I go wrong (I'm not a coder, just a hack :face_with_diagonal_mouth:)

    {# Blog post #}
    &lt;div class="content-wrapper"&gt;

&lt;article class="blog-post"&gt;
  {% set featured_tag = content.topic_list | first %}
  {% if featured_tag %}
  &lt;span class="blog-post__preheader"&gt;{{ featured_tag }}&lt;/span&gt;
  {% endif %}

  &lt;div class="blog-post__columns"&gt;
    &lt;div class="blog-post__column"&gt;
      &lt;h1 class="blog-post__title" style="color: #C5020B;"&gt;{{ content.name }}&lt;/h1&gt;

      {% if theme.blog.show_summary %}
      &lt;p class="blog-post__summary"&gt;{{ content.meta_description|striptags }}&lt;/p&gt;
      {% endif %}

      &lt;div class="blog-post__meta"&gt;
        {% if content.blog_post_author.avatar %}
        &lt;div class="blog-post__avatar" style="background-image: url('{{ content.blog_post_author.avatar }}');"&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        {% endif %}

        &lt;div class="blog-post__author"&gt;
          &lt;a href="{{ blog_author_url(group.id, content.blog_post_author.slug) }}"&gt;
            {{ content.blog_post_author.display_name }}
          &lt;/a&gt;
          &lt;div class="blog-post__timestamp"&gt;
            {{ content.publish_date | datetimeformat('%b %e, %Y') }}
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;

   &lt;hr class="blog-post__divider" /&gt;

 &lt;!-- First Column Blog body copy starts here --&gt;

        &lt;div class="blog-post__body-wrapper col-lg-8 col-sm-12"&gt;

          &lt;div class="blog-post__body" &gt;
            {{ content.post_body }}
